What you need to know:

Coming back after a 19-year hiatus, the WRC Safari Rally will display Kenya’s fauna and flora to a global television and digital audience estimated at 70 million.First in line, of course, is President Uhuru Kenyatta who is also the rally’s patron. He has worked tirelessly to ensure the Safari is back on the global calendar.President Kenyatta has been ably assisted by Sports Cabinet Secretary Amina Mohamed whose performance in this docket has been outstanding, reminiscent of the hard work Maina Kamanda put in during his shift. 